    "body": "> > Thanks for opening this issue. It is being worked on as part of #4641\r\n> \r\n> * How is this issue related to [Support content negotiation of light client data served via rest api #4641](https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/pull/4641) ? This issue reports incorrect data between Nimbus and Lodestar\r\n\r\n@dapplion On first glance it looked like the issue would build on #4641 specifically changes needed to include the version and also the testing, that it thought it would be duplicated effort implementing it separately.  Once I started the implementation It ended up not overlapping 100%. \r\n\r\nIt is implemented now on the branch and I think the most pragmatic thing to do is to move forward with that PR. I don't think spending time to separate into two PR's will be an effective use of time.\r\n\r\nPlus that PR has been open for the past 2 months. And as you also mentioned in the comment, it does what it should do. So holding back not reviewing and merging does not give us anything beneficial since the more we wait, the more lodestar API is not compliant with the spec. The technical optimisation can be added later.",
