    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> It is implemented now on the branch and I think the most pragmatic thing to do is to move forward with that PR. \r\n\r\nI do not agree with the design decisions of #4641 so if the fix it there it would be delayed unnecessarily. It not a good idea to add bug fixes on feature PR and not split.\r\n\r\n> I don't think spending time to separate into two PR's will be an effective use of time.\r\n\r\nI just re-wrote the EIP-4844 PR (3,500 lines) into 17 separate PRs (for now) and doing so helped up the code quality significantly plus we are having progress since most are already merged or close to, while the big one is still stuck. I do think it's a great use of time to split PRs when it makes sense even completely re-writing them if necessary.\r\n\r\n",
