    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> I just re-wrote the EIP-4844 PR (3,500 lines) into 17 separate PRs (for now) and doing so helped up the code quality significantly plus we are having progress since most are already merged or close to, while the big one is still stuck. I do think it's a great use of time to split PRs when it makes sense even completely re-writing them if necessary.\r\n\r\nSure. a PR touching 3,500 lines implementing a crucial feature like EIP-4844 should be split. I see the value in that.\r\n\r\nBut for a PR of 500 lines (20 files), that contains changes that can, for all intents and purposes, be reviewed at once and merged in, safe for your reservation regarding a pre-existing technical limitation? I would go about it differently. And don't get me wrong. It is not as if I believe PRs should not be scoped properly, I already explained why this ended up co-mingled in previous comments.  \r\n\r\nBut I guess we disagree.\r\n\r\nAnyways, here is a separate PR https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/pull/4877 that adds versioning to the LC API. Please help review 🙏    \r\n",
